name: The Home Depot
description: Chain home improvement retailer for tools, appliances & other products (some offer truck rentals).
address: The Home Depot, 2388 Cambie St, Vancouver, BC V5Z 2T8

featured_reviews.review_id: Another Clean Home Depot! Everything is well arranged and their staff were helpful! Was a bit confused where the entrance was but found it after. I always go to their Richmond location which, is as clean and well arranged as this location as well. The person who helped me was really helpful and considerate. I just forgot his name. :( Keep it up team!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Customer service at place is .

Wanted to get colors for our first wooden paint project, the person was really helpful and gave so much detailed knowledge about different types of colors and  what and when to use. Wish could remember his name. But he was at the colour section and made everything so easy. Thanks to him this project is coming out really good
We forgot one of the paint bottle at the payment counter but the lady Name Dolly came all the way to parking lot to give the forgotten color. That kind is service is really rear this days. Thanks again The Home Depot Cambie. For such a great experience.

featured_reviews.review_id: This morning when I arrived just before the store opened at 7am a young man was watering the plants outside, smiled and wished me good morning. Then when the store opened he let me know I could go in. When I walked into the store I was greeted with friendly helpful staff. This was a testament to the staff working at this store and it was a great start to my day. Thank you!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Your service is garbage. Why post items as available both in-store and/or online when they are not available for either?

I went to the store and could not find what I needed, I was told the computer showed 3 in store but they could not find them. I was advised other stores have it and that I should look for it elsewhere.

I purchased a circular saw online for store pick up the next day and my order was accepted but the next day it was cancelled. The next day, I online purchased a tool kit (offered on the website for delivery) and I paid extra for same-day delivery. Again my order was accepted and later it was cancelled. I guess I'll keep my money then!

Why offer products and services you can not provide. Just mark them as unavailable everywhere and don't waste anyone's time.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I had the opportunity to deal with a fantastic employee at this location, her name is Ana B. and she is in appliances, I needed a new washing machine but had to tackle a small adjustment at my apartment to accommodate this new washer. She connected me with a tradesman and got me signed up for a HD credit card which provided incentives for using it, she literally handled everything. I'd love to find out how I can let her employer know how great and informed she was but this seems to be the only platform ...
.

featured_reviews.review_id: I really like this Home Depot store. It's smaller and don't have all the products compared to  the other locations but is so convenient and close of many other things. On the same complex you can find Winners, Save-on-foods and lots of other small stores. Some staff are really helpful but some of them aren't that friendly with people trying some DIY like myself. The parking cost $3 for the first hour and they don't refund it anymore (no matter how much you spend).

featured_reviews.review_id:
Love this branch! We've been coming here for over 3 times now and every staff we met was friendly, patient and super helpful!!!

We were able to replace our blinds and find drywall materials with staff's help. Will come back for other purposes too. Thank you to the staff who helped us! :)

featured_reviews.review_id: Today I had the worst customer service experience of my life at this location. I give Mr.Kireeti a 0/10 review in terms of taking care of the customer avoid him at all times. After giving me a hard time picking up my order he refused to call another supervisor and told me he is the boss here and he's not going to give me my pre paid order keeping me waiting for 50 minutes he still did not apologize. I love shopping at The Home Depot but unfortunately after my interaction with Mr.Kireeti I feel sorry for the company that has chosen such unprofessional and childish person to represent their business. Not only I'm not satisfied but I'm disappointed in the training process and how the management team is being such bad role models for the other employees.
